            "type": "devotion",
            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3ESatan%20is%20a%20master%20at%20dangling%20lustful%20sin%20in%20front%20of%20us%20and%20making%20it%20look%20incredibly%20enticing.%20Then%2C%20after%20we%20reach%20out%20and%20take%20it%2C%20the%20reality%20of%20that%20sin%20is%20a%20miserable%20disappointment.%20How%20quickly%20our%20eyes%20despise%20what%20we%20have%20attained%20through%20lust!%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3ESatan%20tempts%20us%20with%20a%20picture%20of%20sin%20that%20looks%20like%20an%20oasis%20in%20the%20desert.%20He%20makes%20it%20seem%20as%20though%20a%20lust%20fulfilled%20will%20bring%20the%20ultimate%20happiness.%20Amnon%20fantasized%20for%20a%20long%20time%20about%20having%20relations%20with%20Tamar.%20However%2C%20the%20moment%20he%20acted%20upon%20his%20fantasy%2C%20the%20imagined%20sweet%20taste%20of%20it%20turned%20to%20bitterness.%20Amnon%20eventually%20despised%20what%20he%20had%20conquered%20(2%20Samuel%2013%3A15).%20%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EIn%20any%20temptation%2C%20ask%20God%20to%20show%20you%20the%20reality%20of%20how%20disappointing%20the%20sin%20will%20be.%20Any%20move%20you%20make%20because%20of%20lust%20will%20turn%20to%20mock%20you%20and%20will%20lead%20you%20toward%20even%20more%20sin.%20Ask%20for%20the%20help%20of%20the%20Holy%20Spirit%20to%20break%20through%20any%20fantasy%20in%20your%20mind%20and%20to%20see%20its%20backside%3A%20anger%2C%20disrespect%2C%20and%20even%20death.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%22There%20is%20a%20path%20before%20each%20person%20that%20seems%20right%2C%20but%20it%20ends%20in%20death%22%20(Proverbs%2014%3A12).%20Don't%20fall%20for%20Satan's%20bait!%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
